<AbstractNarration>Research Experiences for Undergraduates in Mathematics at Indiana University will provide twelve undergraduate mathematics majors with a research topic and a research environment so that they have an active eight week experience involving mathematical research.  The students will face the intellectual challenges of learning more about a mathematical topic and developing approaches and solutions for unsolved &lt;br/&gt;questions at a research level.  This research experience will enhance the students' perspective on mathematics and provide impressions of how mathematical knowledge is evolving.  It will also be a valuable &lt;br/&gt;experience in actively finding results and communicating their work to their peers.&lt;br/&gt;</AbstractNarration>
